Bring a large #pot{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Roughly chop the @black olives{4}. Slice the @red chilli{1} in half lengthways and remove the seeds. Very finely dice the chilli (then wash your hands!).

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #pan{} on medium heat. Once hot add a pinch of the red chilli (more depending how hot you like it).

After ~{60%seconds} add the @chopped tomatoes{1%tin}, the olives and the @lilliput capers{1/tin}. Refill the tin a quarter with @water{1/4%cup}, swirl around and add this to the sauce too. Stir in the @tomato puree{1%tbsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}(if you have some) and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Turn the heat to medium-low and leave to simmer gently.

Put your @linguine{220%g} in your #pot{} of water and cook it for around ~{10%mins} or until 'al dente'.

> Pasta is 'al dente' when it is soft enough to eat yet has a slight firmness left in the middle.

Drain the pasta once it is ready but keep back @pasta water{1/4%cup}.

Once the pasta is ready roughly chop the @basil{1/2%bunch} and add three quarters into the sauce.

Tip the drained pasta into the sauce along with your @baby spinach{2%bunch} and toss the pan to mix everything. If you need to loosen the sauce a little, add a dash of the reserved pasta water.

> You can stir the ingredients gently if you're afraid you might paint the walls!

Put a #lid{} on the pan for ~{3%minutes} to allow the spinach to steam.

Serve with plenty of @hard Italian style cheese{2%tbsp}(grated) and the remaining basil.